>>e5372c74-81d7-4999-bf46-80de1cb68e5c
We can see it, it simply does not beg comment. It is not detailed enough to be "good" but proportionally appropriate enough to not be "bad". It's one of those pics that ends up in albums but nobody really likes or brings up in image dumps. 
Be a bit more daring in your design, a bit more thorough in your texture, or a bit more imaginative in your composition.
In short, it's a dreaded ''5/10.''

>>1ee35312-a2b8-4b28-907a-588582eb93fb
I do like the cable face though, missed that. 5.1/10
Oh good, you guys are still around.

Things have come full circle. Every time I look at this site I'm reminded of old screen caps of the first posts of /b/, where everyone has a tripcode and nobody knows what they're doing. That chan magic is strong here, so potent it burns the nostril . 
Oh, to be a newfag again, bright eyed and bushy tailed, oblivious to conventions or dogma. At the same time we're as jaded as possible, wisest of all. We embody the Fool and Hermit at once. In time I suspect we'll pick up the wand once more and cast a hex even stronger than ebola-chan.
